<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Voice capabilities</h2>
	<ul class="features-grid">
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "telephone" %}</span>
			<h3>Origination and Termination</h3>
			<p>Run inbound and outbound voice through VoiceTel with published rate keys, routing controls, and carrier-support escalation paths.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "broadcast-pin" %}</span>
			<h3>Intelligent Routing</h3>
			<p>Anycast routes traffic to the nearest or best available node among multiple nodes advertising the same address — commonly used for DNS, CDNs, and resilient network services. Geocast routes traffic to nodes within a specific geographic area, helping deliver ultra-low-latency, high-quality voice by keeping media paths local and efficient.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "diagram-3" %}</span>
			<h3>Diverse Path Routing</h3>
			<p>Diverse inbound routing tries multiple network paths, carriers, or routes until a successful one is found. This improves reliability by avoiding failed, congested, or poor-quality routes, automatically switching to an alternate path, and pinholing the last hop to maintain a stable final connection.</p>
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

